cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel query method for social search based on topic modeling. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with social streams and influence scores. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes two approximation algorithms for real-time processing of the proposed query method. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also possible as the paper uses topic modeling to represent user queries and elements in the topic space. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes two algorithms for processing the proposed query method.
